Here's a JavaScript function that extracts the text from a document:

```javascript
function extractTextFromDocument() {
  // Get the document's body element
  const body = document.body;

  // Get all the text nodes in the body element
  const textNodes = body.querySelectorAll('*').reduce((acc, el) => {
    const textContent = el.textContent.trim();
    if (textContent) {
      acc.push(el);
    }
    return acc;
  }, []);

  // Extract the text from each text node
  const text = textNodes.reduce((acc, el) => {
    acc += el.textContent.trim();
    return acc;
  }, '');

  // Return the extracted text
  return text;
}
```

This function works by first getting the document's body element. It then gets all the text nodes in the body element. Finally, it extracts the text from each text node and returns the extracted text.

