To directly download a page using its URL in the browser console, follow these steps:

1. Open the browser console by pressing F12 or right-clicking on the page and selecting "Inspect Element".

2. In the console, type the following command:

```
fetch('https://example.com').then(response => response.blob()).then(blob => {
  const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  const a = document.createElement('a');
  a.href = url;
  a.download = 'example.html';
  a.click();
  URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
});
```

3. Replace the URL in the command with the URL of the page you want to download.

4. Press Enter to execute the command.

5. The page will be downloaded as a file with the name you specified in the command.

